Type assertions are useful when you have data that is coming from an external source or from user input, and you need to perform some validation or casting before using it in your code. It's important to note that type assertions are essentially telling the TypeScript compiler to trust your judgment about the actual type of a value, so you should use them with caution and only when you are sure that you know the actual type of the value.

